      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions agree with bench measurements within combined uncertainty at all five operating points. One operating point exhibits a wide 95% CI of ±18% on the predicted hemolysis index. This width is driven by epistemic uncertainty in the power-law hemolysis model exponent (α), quantified via Monte Carlo sampling of the published coefficient distribution from Giersiepen et al. The wide bound is honestly documented in the sensitivity analysis and carried forward explicitly in the decision rationale. It does not prevent acceptance because even the upper bound of the CI remains below the clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100 mL. Gradation 4 achieved."
