      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence closure is selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating blood-contacting devices. A turbulence model sensitivity study quantifies ±9% variation in predicted hemolysis index relative to RSM and k-ε realisable closures. This variation is explicitly included in the Monte Carlo uncertainty ensemble and does not drive the upper CI bound above the clinical threshold. Gradation 4 achieved."
