      "rationale": "All model inputs are sourced from calibrated measurements or peer-reviewed literature. Uncertainty bounds are assigned to each input parameter. A 10,000-sample Monte Carlo study propagates input uncertainty through the full CFD-hemolysis pipeline to the hemolysis index QoI. The dominant contributor identified in the sensitivity analysis is the power-law hemolysis model exponent α (Sobol index 0.61), which is responsible for the wide CI at one operating point. This is explicitly documented. Gradation 4 achieved."
